Kenya's High Commissioner to the UK Manoah Esipisu has been appointed Chairperson of the Executive Committee of the Board of Governors at the 54-member Commonwealth Secretariat. The announcement was made on Friday. The Commonwealth Secretariat is the main intergovernmental agency and central institution of the Commonwealth of Nations, according to Wikipedia. It is responsible for facilitating co-operation between members; organising meetings, including the Commonwealth Heads of Government Meetings (CHOGM); assisting and advising on policy development; and providing assistance to countries in implementing the decisions and policies of the Commonwealth. The Secretariat has observer status in the United Nations General Assembly. It is located at Marlborough House in London, the United Kingdom, a former royal residence that was given by Queen Elizabeth II, Head of the Commonwealth. Esipisu is a former State House spokesman. He served since President Uhuru Kenyatta's election in 2013 and was nominated for the High Commissioner position in 2018.